              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-SYS",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The systematic uncertainty is  between  5.8",
                " and  7.2  %,  as determined by the neutron detection",
                " efficiency (5%), the number of incident LCS gamma-rays",
                " (3 %), and the electron beam size effect (< 4.2 %)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Cross sections   of the   139La(g,n)  and  141Pr(g,n)",
                " reactions were  measured  using  quasi-monochromatic",
                " g-ray beams   from   laser  Compton  scattering.  No",
                " evidence  for  sufficient  thermonuclear   p-process",
                " contribution to  the  rare odd-odd nuclide 138La was",
                " found."
              ]
            }
          ],
